[B] Explicit formula: sum over first K zeros of 2 Re(6^rho / rho)
    under RH-assumption Re(rho) = 1/2.  target (from residual in
    riemann_explicit.hexa round-1 era)  was diff ~ 0.0818 for K=inf.
    Convergence partial sums:
      K=5   sum_K = 0.170142
      K=10   sum_K = 0.0227889
      K=15   sum_K = 0.126986
      K=20   sum_K = 0.0629358
      K=25   sum_K = 0.0479759
      K=30   sum_K = 0.141074
      K=35   sum_K = 0.0584615
      K=40   sum_K = 0.0262131
      K=45   sum_K = 0.100446
      K=50   sum_K = 0.113798
    honesty: truncation error decays slowly (~ 1/gamma); K=50 not
    enough to match the x=6 residual to full precision. Direction
    of partial sums stable -> no numerical RH violation detected.

